description: A woman in her 20s dies in the crash, which also left two men seriously injured.
title: Two men arrested after woman dies in Market Harborough crash
title_page: Two men arrested after woman dies in Market Harborough crash - BBC News
maintext:
Two men have been arrested after a woman in her 20s was killed when a car left the road in Leicestershire.
A black Seat Leon with three people inside left the A6 in Market Harborough and overturned just before 01:30 GMT on Monday.
The woman was pronounced dead at the scene and two men who were in the car were taken to hospital after suffering serious injuries.
Leicestershire Police said no other vehicle was involved and appealed for witnesses after officers arrested two men, aged 21 and 19, on suspicion of causing death by dangerous driving.
